# Agent Harness

This project has reusable Cursor agent infrastructure installed by `agent-harness`.

## Managed Files

The harness manages:

- `AGENTS.md`
- `.cursor/rules/agent-critic-trigger.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/agent-critic.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/agent-harness.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/agent-learnings.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/pipeline-trigger.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/pipeline.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/supabase.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/zustand-store-architecture.mdc`
- `.cursor/skills/**`
- `.cursor/hooks.json`
- `.cursor/hooks/file-scope-guard.sh`
- `.cursor/hooks/tool-scope-guard.sh`
- `.cursor/hooks/subagent-audit.sh`

The installer records hashes in `.cursor/agent-harness-manifest.json` and treats edited managed files as local modifications.

## Operating Guidance

- Keep project-specific instructions in `AGENTS.md` or new local rules.
- Keep harness-managed files generic unless intentionally forking them.
- If the user mentions `#critic`, read `.cursor/rules/agent-critic.mdc` before acting.
- If the user mentions `#implements`, read `.cursor/rules/pipeline.mdc` before acting.
- Do not bypass approval gates defined in the pipeline rule.
- Read `agent-learnings.mdc` before implementation and update it when you fix a repeatable mistake.
